             Another ballbreaker by MAD MEL.............

PRINTING INFO:  
     To make a complete document, you will need to first print out the file
"PoolCode.pic."  Use DPaint or your favorite paint program.  Start the
print at the top of the page.  Then print this file on the line directly
below where the picture leaves off.  When printing this file, be sure to
set your column guides for 1 left and 80 right.  (in your prefs)  Use
Diamond 12pnt for your font.  Before printing the file, cut this printing
part out.
     If you do correctly, you should have a one sheet code doc.  The bottom
set of codes should be neet and in three even columns.  If not, try again. 
I used the following: Photon paint to print the picture. Excellence to
print the text file.

Excellence Page Settings:
Top and header at 0
Bottom at 0.1
Footer at 0
Left Margin at 0.2
Right Margin at 0.4
Page 11 x 8.5

Font at Diamond 12pnt Normal print

Preferences for printer Tractor, Columns at 1 L and 80 R.  
Normal Pica etc.

Good Luck.......MM.
